<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC is effecting its crackdown on crypto m=
ostly by going after crypto exchanges. The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/34044144.259401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS=
9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMDcvd2hlbi1pcy1hLXRva2VuLW5vdC1hLXNlY3Vya=
XR5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMTgyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJj=
ZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDExOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cC211cfb85" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  thinking is roughly</a>:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If all of these crypto tokens are sec=
urities, then not only were they all=C2=A0<em>issued </em>illegally (by iss=
uers that didn=E2=80=99t register them with the SEC), but they all=C2=A0<em=
>trade=C2=A0</em>illegally (on crypto exchanges that have not registered wi=
th the SEC as national securities exchanges).</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bo=
ttom: 5px;">There are fewer crypto exchanges than crypto issuers, and they =
are bigger, and shutting them down will shut down crypto much more efficien=
tly than going after all the issuers one by one.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One of the SEC=E2=80=99s main targets is Coinb=
ase Global=C2=A0Inc., the big US exchange. The SEC <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34044144.259401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZX=
JnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMDYvdGhlLXNlYy1jb21lcy1mb3ItY3J5c=
HRvP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMTgyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJj=
ZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDExOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cB86d32551" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  sued Coinbase in June</a>, and Coi=
nbase is fighting the case hard. Yesterday a New York federal judge held a =
hearing on Coinbase=E2=80=99s motion to dismiss the SEC=E2=80=99s case, and=
 it sounds like it went pretty well for Coinbase. <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34044144.259401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9=
maW5hbmNlL3JlZ3VsYXRpb24vanVkZ2UtcXVlc3Rpb25zLXNlY3MtY2xhaW0tdG8tcmVndWxhdG=
UtY29pbmJhc2UtYWUyZjI0MGM_bW9kPWl0cF93c2o/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB876bc474=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;"> The Wall Street Journal reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A federal judge on Wednesday questioned whethe=
r allowing the Securities and Exchange Commission to impose its regulations=
 on Coinbase would give the agency sway over markets it doesn=E2=80=99t hav=
e authority to supervise.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI want to understand how your standar=
d does not sweep in the collectible market or commodities,=E2=80=9D U.S. Di=
strict Judge Katherine Polk Failla told SEC lawyers in the courtroom. =E2=
=80=9CIt is a real fear that I have that your argument is just sweeping too=
 broadly.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Failla is considering Coinbase=E2=80=99s reque=
st to dismiss the SEC=E2=80=99s civil lawsuit against it filed in Manhattan=
 federal court. She didn=E2=80=99t rule at the end of Wednesday=E2=80=99s f=
ive-hour hearing but is expected to decide in the coming months.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But even if Coinbase wins, there=E2=80=99s som=
ething a little hollow about the victory. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/34044144.259401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMTcvY29pbmJhc2UtYXJndWVzLWNyeXB0by1saWtlLWJlYW=
5pZS1iYWJpZXMtaW4tc2VjLWNhc2UtaGVhcmluZz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMTE4MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGR=
iZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDAxMTgm=
dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBeff83f58" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  Bloomberg News reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">William Savitt, a lawyer for Coinbase, told US=
 District Judge Katherine Polk Failla that tokens trading on the exchange a=
ren=E2=80=99t securities subject to SEC jurisdiction because buyers don=E2=
=80=99t gain any rights as a part of their purchases, as they do with stock=
s or bonds.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s the difference between b=
uying Beanie Babies Inc. and buying Beanie Babies,=E2=80=9D Savitt said. =
=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Lawyers for the government responded that buyi=
ng an item like a baseball card or a figurine doesn=E2=80=99t mean that som=
eone is buying a stake in the enterprise that makes such items.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But they said that wasn=E2=80=99t the case wit=
h tokens sold on Coinbase.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWhen they buy this token, they are in=
vesting into the network behind it,=E2=80=9D SEC lawyer Patrick Costello sa=
id. =E2=80=9COne cannot be separated from the other.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC=E2=80=99s argument here is that crypto=
 tokens are an investment, promising some upside from some business buildin=
g some network with some potential to do good things. Coinbase=E2=80=99s ar=
gument <em>is that they aren=E2=80=99t</em>, that it lists tokens that give=
 investors no rights and that have no claim on any economic activity. Coinb=
ase=E2=80=99s argument is that crypto is a trillion-dollar market for Beani=
e Babies, that it is not a way to raise money to fund real business ideas b=
ut simply a way to gamble on collectibles. =E2=80=9CNo, see, if you buy a c=
rypto token, you get nothing, so there=E2=80=99s nothing for the SEC to reg=
ulate.=E2=80=9D A good legal argument! But weird=C2=A0<em>marketing</em>!</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The problem for crypto is that, to have a big =
attractive financial market in the long term, you need to have obligations.=
 You need to have some system for ensuring that investors get what they pay=
 for, that entrepreneurs have duties to the investors who give them money, =
that people deal honestly, that investors get disclosure.<a class=3D"footno=
te-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: no=
ne !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bord=
er-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important;=
 display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a> And Coinbase, to be clear, has called for those things: It=C2=A0<em>wa=
nts=C2=A0</em>regulation=C2=A0of crypto, because in the long run that is go=
od for its business; it has <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/34044144.259401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9maWxlcy9ydWxlcy9wZXRpd=
GlvbnMvMjAyMi9wZXRuNC03ODkucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb5ee37d4" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 begged the SEC</a> to write new rules for crypto. And I <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34044144.259401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxv=
b21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMTMvY3J5cHRvLXdhbnRzLXNvbWU=
tc2VjLXJ1bGVzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMTgyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdX=
RtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDExOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzd=
HVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc7024639" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  have=C2=A0sympathized =
with its view</a> that some new rules would be nice.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the SEC <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/34044144.259401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3N0=
YXRlbWVudC9nZW5zbGVyLWNvaW5iYXNlLXBldGl0aW9uLTEyMTUyMw/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB50e853fc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> rejected that request</a>, saying, no, actually, th=
e <em>existing=C2=A0</em>rules apply to crypto, and are fine. But the crypt=
o market mostly=C2=A0<em>doesn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>want existing SEC regula=
tions =E2=80=94=C2=A0the disclosure and anti-fraud rules that apply to stoc=
k =E2=80=94 to apply to crypto, because they would be too restrictive. (Tha=
t=E2=80=99s why Coinbase is fighting the SEC in court, arguing that the SEC=
 has no jurisdiction over crypto at all.) It would be good for crypto to ha=
ve some rules to eliminate some frauds and make the market more trustworthy=
, but if you have too many rules and eliminate too many frauds =E2=80=A6 we=
ll, you might worry,=C2=A0what will be left?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Coinbase itself went public in 2021, its =
chief executive officer, Brian Armstrong, wrote <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34044144.259401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9Bc=
mNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE2Nzk3ODgvMDAwMTYyODI4MDIxMDA2ODUwL2NvaW5iYXNlZ2xv=
YmFsaW5jNDI0Yi5odG0jaWVhYWUzNjI2MDNjZjQwYmZhMGJlZjhhMzgzYmFjZDY2XzMx/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB5658b66e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> a letter to investors</a>. It was ful=
l of big claims:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Coinbase is a company with an ambitious vision=
: to create more economic freedom for every person and business. Everyone d=
eserves access to financial services that can help empower them to create a=
 better life for themselves and their families, but today we are a long way=
 from this vision. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What started with Bitcoin has spawned an entir=
e industry with countless different blockchains and tokens. We now have sta=
blecoins, privacy coins, security tokens, reward tokens, governance tokens,=
 and smart contracts. We=E2=80=99re seeing the digitization of all types of=
 value in a new economy that we call the cryptoeconomy.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Trading and speculation were the first major u=
se cases to take off in cryptocurrency, just like people rushed to buy doma=
in names in the early days of the internet. But we=E2=80=99re now seeing cr=
yptocurrency evolve into something much more important. People are using cr=
yptocurrency to earn, spend, save, stake, borrow, lend, vote, and perform m=
any other types of economic activity. Companies are being funded, getting e=
arly customers, and will eventually go public, all on the blockchain. The c=
ryptoeconomy is just getting started. It is not intended to replace the tra=
ditional economy, but instead to be a complement to it, much like email was=
 to paper mail. The cryptoeconomy offers a more global, free, and fair alte=
rnative to traditional economies that is native to the internet.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now it=E2=80=99s Beanie Babies.</p>
