<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An important meta-story that you could tell ab=
out financial markets over the past few years would be that, for a long tim=
e, interest rates were roughly zero, which means that=C2=A0<em>discount rat=
es=C2=A0</em>were low: A dollar in the distant future was worth about as mu=
ch as a dollar today. Therefore, investors ascribed a lot of value to very =
long-term stuff, and were not particularly concerned about short-term profi=
tability. Low discount rates made speculative distant-future profits worth =
more and steady current profits worth less.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then interest rates went up rapidly starti=
ng in 2022, and everyone=E2=80=99s priorities shifted. A dollar today is no=
w worth a lot more than a dollar in 10 years. People prioritize profits tod=
ay over speculation in the future.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is a popular story to tell about the boom=
 in, for instance, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/34044144.259401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLz=
IwMjMtMDMtMTAvc3RhcnR1cC1iYW5rLWhhZC1hLXN0YXJ0dXAtYmFuay1ydW4_Y21waWQ9QkJEM=
DExODI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXIm=
dXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwMTE4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cB6aa3cf23" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;"> tech startups, or crypto</a>: =E2=80=9CStartups are a=
 low-interest-rate phenomenon.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0In 2020, people had a lot of m=
oney and a lot of patience, so they were willing to invest in speculative p=
ossibly-world-changing ideas that would take a long time to pay out. (Or to=
 fund startups that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/34044144.259401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzL=
zIwMjItMTEtMDcvbW92aWVwYXNzLXdhcy1ub3QtYS1nb29kLWJ1c2luZXNzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAx=
MTgyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV=
0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDExOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB5107ae45" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;"> lost money on every transaction</a> in the long-term p=
ursuit of market share.) In 2022, the Fed raised rates, people=E2=80=99s pr=
eferences changed, and the startup and crypto bubbles popped.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suppose, though, that you could tell a simil=
ar story about environmental investing? Climate change is, plausibly, a ver=
y large and very long-term threat to a lot of businesses. If you just go ar=
ound doing everything normally this year, probably rising oceans won=E2=80=
=99t wash away your factories=C2=A0<em>this year</em>. But maybe they will =
in 2040. Maybe you should invest today in making your factories ocean-proof=
,=C2=A0or in cutting carbon emissions so the oceans don=E2=80=99t rise: Tha=
t will cost you some money today, but will save you some money in 2040. Is =
it worth it? Well, depends on the discount rate. If rates are low, you will=
 care more about 2040. If rates are high, you will care more about saving m=
oney today.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/34044144.259401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
